The article is a transcript of a speech given by the President at the signing of an executive decree for the White House Program for Hispanic Education Excellence. The President emphasizes the importance of improving education opportunities and outcomes for Hispanic students in the United States. He discusses the challenges faced by the Hispanic community in education and outlines various initiatives and reforms aimed at addressing these issues. The President also calls for collective efforts from the government, private sector, teachers, parents, and students to ensure that every child has access to a quality education and the opportunity to fulfill their potential. He concludes by expressing his commitment to fulfilling the promise of a better life for all children in the country.